SYMPTOM_TEXT: On April 8th at 4am, I woke up feeling a strong pain in my heart / esophagus region. I was alone and out of town and didn't know what to do, so I just sat in the hotel bed and waited for morning to come. I didn't know if i was having a heart attack or if it was gas from drinking soda the previous day. I went to work. At work, the left side of my tongue suddenly started swelling and a tingling and numbness set in my upper lip. I was very scared, rushed to the drugstore and bought GasX, Ricola drops (my throat was slightly sore, too) and Allegra 24 hours. I immediately took the Allegra pill but still went to the hospital. When getting to the parking of the hospital, though, the anti-allergic started kicking in and the tongue started getting back to normal, so I went back to work and didn't enter the hospital. I was ok for a while. Hours later, rashes started showing all over my body. Starting in my arms then under my breasts. On the night of the 8th, I even had fever and chills. Still, I had to go to work so it was a real nightmare. I also had diarreah. I then went to the drugstore again and also bought regular and night Advil, lots of water and electrolytes drink, Peptobismol and Benadryl (only Allegra was not enough). The following day, April 9th, the rashes started spreading all over my body, the fever was only being controlled by Advil. I flew back to Miami and was bedridden until the April the 11th. On the night of April the 11th I still woke up with very strong headache and on the 12th spent the day with a headache, but since have gotten better.
LAB_DATA: COVID test on April 8th and 11th: both negative.
OTHER_MEDS: Birth control (Yasmin),  Melatonin, Neocell Keratin supplement, levothyroxine 75 MCG, Topiramate 25mg, MoonJuice Super Hair supplement

Patient has a history of epilepsy. She has not had a seizure since age 13 and is not currently medicated. She received her first dose of Pfizer Covid 19 vaccine into her LEFT DELTOID on 4/5/21 at 8:40 am. Patient left a message on voicemail on 4/11/21 reporting a seizure on 4/10/21 and COVID 19 symptoms (fever, chills, body aches, etc.) The seizure was minimal compared her prior seizure history (she did not lose consciousness and did not require medical intervention).  Patient wanted us to be aware of this issue and see if we recommended proceeding with her second Pfizer Covid 19 shot when due. I spoke to the patient and she told me she had had Covid 19 in February 2020.  We have seen clinical reports of more pronounced reactions to 1st dose vaccines in patients who had the Covid 19 virus and explained that to the patient. I spoke to the patient on 4/14/21 and she was feeling much better.  I recommended to patient that she delay getting her second dose indefinitely.
HISTORY: Adolescent history of epilepsy. No seizures since age 13; no medications taken for disease; no seizure history from other vaccines.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient with prior Covid infection Nov 2020, fully recovered, received first dose Moderna vaccine on 3/13/21 and next day developed body aches, fevers, chills, shortness of breath. Admitted 3/17/21 due to hypoxia, had ground glass opacities on CT. SARS-CoV-2 PCR negative x 2.  Vigorous immune response could have caused lung inflammation and hypoxia, similar to a covid infection, but from the vaccine. 60YM with a history of a chronic inflammatory arthritis on methotrexate, hospitalization in November 2020 with Covid pneumonia, he was discharged on 1 to 2 L of home oxygen, and reports that he was told by his PCP about a month after discharge that he was able to come off the oxygen as his oxygen saturations had normalized.  He returned to his usual state of health and activity with no issues until he received the first dose of his Moderna covid-19 vaccine through his primary care office on 3/13.  The next day he developed arm pain and then progressive body aches, headaches, fevers, chills, and shortness of breath.  He presented to the ER and was found to be febrile with hypoxia and admitted for treatment and evaluation.   Acute hypoxemic respiratory failure with ground glass opacities on CT : oxygen 87% on RA in ER, 84% on room air 3/19, resolves with oxygen support of 2lpm.  CTA was negative for pulmonary embolism. SARS-CoV-2 PCR negative x2 as well as respiratory virus panel, CT shows ground glass opacities, patient was started on ceftriaxone and doxycycline for empiric treatment for possible community-acquired pneumonia, although procalcitonin was negative.  BNP was elevated at 458, so an echocardiogram was performed which showed a normal EF, and grade 1 diastolic dysfunction.  Patient was given 2 doses of furosemide during the hospitalization and BNP normalized. Patient was started on prednisone to calm down a possible inflammatory response triggered by the COVID-19 vaccine in a person who likely already has antibodies, causing hypoxia.  With this patient significantly improved and at discharge is on room air at rest, but still requires 2 L/min with exertion.  CRP was markedly elevated, supporting an inflammatory process.  Autoimmune lung disease panel was sent and is in process at time of discharge.  Patient requested discharge home, Discharged on a slow prednisone taper to avoid rebound with abrupt discontinuation of steroids.  Patient will complete 2 additional days of Augmentin and doxycycline at discharge.
LAB_DATA: CTA 3/17/21  IMPRESSION:  1. No acute or chronic pulmonary embolism.  2. Bilateral upper lobe groundglass density. Imaging features can be seen with  COVID-19 pneumonia, though are nonspecific and can occur with a variety of infectious and noninfectious processes.. 3. Mild cardiomegaly . 4. Thoracic ankylosis.       Blood cultures 3/18/21 - NEGATIVE        3/18 & 3/19 Cocci IgG IgM Neg; Influenza A (PCR) NEG; Influenza B (PCR) NEG; RSV (PCR) NEG; S Pneumo Ag urine NEG; SARS-Cov-2 PCR NEG  .
HISTORY: Ankylosis of spine     Hx of total hip arthroplasty   Chronic hip pain   Chronic immunosuppression on methotrexate, ?RA

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Anaphylactoid: throat itching and swelling; loss of voice; nausea; diarrhea.  Throat itching began within the first 5-6 minutes post vaccine; nurses in attendance gave me 25mg Benadryl within first 10 minutes and a second 25mg dose after the next 15 min...the diphenhydramine didn't take effect.  The nurse took my BP and attached a device to monitor my oxygen level.  After another 15 minutes, I felt disoriented, my voice became hoarse and I could barely talk...the nurse told me that my oxygen saturation was still good.  I began to feel nauseated and had stomach cramps and bowel urgency.  At that point, the nurse in attendance brought a wheelchair and took me to the ER, allowing me to stop to use the restroom.  ER physician gave me famotidine 20mg and oral prednisone and watched me for 2+ hours.  When I felt more oriented, they allowed me to go home.  I did not require epinephrine, but the ER physican told me that I should NOT take the second dose.  I followed up at home with  Benadryl 25mg bid for 4 days.  My voice returned in 6 days. I followed up my primary care physician, on Jan. 23rd...she also told me not to take the second dose.  My primary care also advised me NOT to take the second dose.  Please note:  ran a basic  blood panel as a part of my annual physical on Jan. 27th.  The results came back with all my levels totally off the chart!!   She had the test repeated on Feb. 16th and all my levels were back to normal.  She noted that the discrepancy must have been a result of my reaction to the Pfizer vaccine and suggested that she would let her patients know NOT to have bloodwork done within 14 days of their COVID vaccine.
LAB_DATA: No medical tests or lab work was performed in the ER.

The night after the night of my vaccine I had a tightening of my whole left side, from my eye, down my neck, into my shoulder and chest and down left arm.  Then I started to get shooting pain all around my shoulder blades.  I brushed it off thinking that most people had complaints of feeling pain or sick the few days after their vaccines and then they said it went away.  Mine never went away.  After about 5 days it really started to worry me.  The pain was very intense- unbearable even- and i couldnt move my left arm or lie back in any way without incredible pain.  I called urgent care and they told me I could come in if the pain was bad but that maybe I wanted to see my regular physician to see what was going on.  I made an appointment with my doctor but it wasn?t until the end of the next week.  After 8 days, I couldn?t take it anymore.  I went to urgent care- they did an EKG and a chest xray and said all was normal.  They gave me an anti-inflammatory (naproxen) and a muscle relaxer. They took blood and the only thing they noted to me was that I should have my doctor check my platelette count.  They told me they thought it must be muscular.  I went home.  Neither of those medications seemed to help.  The pain was less in the day when I was moving around, but towards the end of the day it was getting so bad (still is) that I can?t sleep or get comfortable.  My doctor did blood work and couldn?t seem to find the source of what was going on with me either.  She prescribed me a new anti-inflammatory (meloxicam), a new muscle relaxer (cyclobenzaprine) and a pain killer (hydrocodone acetamin).  Sometimes those medications help- they knock me out- but when I wake up I feel the same.  I can?t take them in the day because they make me too loopy and tired.  I don?t know what is wrong. I can?t seem to get answers and  nobody can figure it out.  It is definitely my left side. I feel it in ky head, my chest, my shoulder and down my left arm and it has been almost 5 weeks.  It seems to be getting worse not better.  Looking for help or direction please

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Store technician administered 1st COVID-19 Moderna vaccine shot into left arm of "Patient".  Upon disposing the syringe in the Sharps container, employee shortly notifies patient that the syringe was empty with air and says that she needs to administer again.  Patient was uncomfortable with any possibility of potentially getting a second dose of the vaccine by accident since Patient not only reported feeling sensations in her body shortly after the first administration but more so because employee already disposed and delayed momentarily before notifying the Patient of the error.  Patient considered that the only way to confirm for a fact that the shot was empty or not was to look through each of the syringes within the Sharps container to check for evidence of residue (or lack thereof).  Employee managed to retrieve a few syringes and stopped further inspection upon finding a syringe without any evidence of residue from the vaccine.  Employee then proceeded to administer the shot a second time.  Witnesses (store Employees) were present.  Patient proceeded to file a report with the pharmacy manager who stated that she will file a (same day) Quality Assurance report to document the event which will go into their files and a copy will also go to store Corporate.  Patient mentioned to  Manager about retrieving and inspecting each syringe for evidential confirmation and peace of mind that employee had not given any other empty shots that day.  However, after Manager spoke to her supervisor Patient was told it was not possible without the proper tools to handle the biohazardous materials.  Patient remained past her monitoring/observation time for side effects around 12:00PM.
LAB_DATA: Medical tests, laboratory results, or any result or outcome of adverse effects TBD

SYMPTOM_TEXT: This patient was vaccinated with the  vaccine at approx 1530, in the left arm. He was sitting in the observation area for his allotted 15 minutes. At approx 1540 this nurse was called over by a staff member and was told that this patient was feeling dizzy, hot and nauseous. This patient presented as diaphoretic and pale.  RN's, came over to the patient and began asking basic demographic info questions, and started to measure his vital signs. This patient denied any heart issues or past medical history. His father was present and was seated next to the patient. We had the patient move onto a cot and we had the patient lay down and we elevated his feet. The patients initial vital signs were: 110/70, HR 56 and O2 99% at 1543. He stated that he felt some shortness of breath but was able to speak to us without difficulty. No wheezing or rhonchi present. We kept the patients legs elevated and provided a cold pack to his head and neck. After approx 10 minutes the patient stated he felt better, but he felt cold and his legs and upper body were shaking. Once we sat him up into a sitting position he stated he wasn't feeling dizzy. We kept him there for another 10 minutes until he felt better. His vital signs were measured again and his bp was 140/90, HR 91 and O2 level was 99%. The patient denied any difficulty breathing. This nurse advised for the patient and his father to go to the Emergency Room if another episode of this occurs. The patient understood and he walked with his father to their car without any difficulty.

A few hours after I got home from getting the shot, my lower body started to ache super bad. My skin started to hurt like I had rug burn, but I wasn't surprised because that happens to me when I get the flu. My legs and groin region started to hurt more and more and I got the chills. It was extremely bad and I was sort of writhing but I told myself I was overreacting. At around 8 or 9, I decided I would sleep it off and went to bed. At 1:00 am, I got up to use the bathroom and I began feeling lightheaded. I thought I had just stood up to fast so I continued. As I walked, i got more and more dizzy and I couldn't hear well. When I sat on the toilet, I realized I wasn't going to be able to get back up, so I sat and waited. I started to get super hot so I took my shirt off. I finally was able to get up and walked towards the sink but I collapsed before I got there. I started drinking the sink water and ran my shirt under the water and put it on my head to cool off.  This really helped so I went back to my room to call my mom. I have never fainted before or come this close to fainting. For the rest of the night I had the worst migrane of my life that gave me aura in my left eye and made my left arm and left side of my face go numb, as well as pulsing in my head. The pain on my skin, and in my legs and head was still there for two days after but it was manageable enough for me to go about my day. I tried to exercize to ease the muscle pain but this did not work.

Within several minutes of the injection, I noticed a strange taste in my mouth.  A few minutes later my tongue became swollen.  Shortly after that I noticed that swallowing was different than normal.   I was still able to breathe normally but thought I should tell someone.  I notified the person who have me the shot and she told me a nurse practitioner would come talk with me.  I told the NP about the strange taste and that I felt like my tongue was swelling up and that swallowing was more difficult than usual.  She asked me a bunch of questions and then told me she would give me a Zyrtec tablet to take home with me in case I needed it later.  I stayed for another 20 minutes and since it didn't get any worse, I told them I thought I was okay to leave.  I took the Zyrtec when I got out to the car and about an hour later the swelling was gone and swallowing was normal again.   On Monday I notified my PCP of what happened and asked her if I should get the second dose in 3 weeks.  She told me should would consult with an allergist and get back to me.
LAB_DATA: None.  I did notify my PCP about my vaccination experience.   I'm not planning to get the second dose unless my PCP says it's okay.

I couldn't take anything other than Tylenol, which didn't seem to help. Lab on 4/12/21 indicated levels were up to 30,000. Day two  after getting the vaccine, I started feeling vertigo and nauseous. I hydrated extensively, and  day three are started to feel a little bit better.  Day four I took a turn for the worse, and the vertigo and nausea intensified.   In the middle of the night, the vertigo was extreme.  I almost checked myself into the ER, but I decided to try to continue sleeping and hopefully feel better in the morning. In the morning, day five, I went to my primary care doctor.  I told her my symptoms, she said possibly due to the vaccine.  She prescribed me meclizine.  I took it in the evening, and did not feel any symptom relief.  In the middle of the night, extreme vertigo again, it was atrocious.   Day six (Saturday), I checked myself into the ER.  They upped my dose of meclizine (to 50 mg).  This new dose also had zero effect on my vertigo/nausea.  I felt vertigo/nausea all day. Speaking to some doctors in the family, they suggested to me that I had developed BPPV. Day seven, woke up again with vertigo/nausea, and it didn?t subside at all as the day went on.  I spoke with my father, and he told me that he had BPPV before apparently.  He drove to my house and did the Eply maneuver on me 10 times throughout the day.  Felt a little bit better.  Scheduled an appt with ENT for following day. Day eight, feeling a little bit better (after eply maneuvers, possibly related).  Visited ENT, he reassured me that the vestibular system is very efficient and I will eventually get better.  Scheduled appt for me for neurologist and MRI for later that day.  Went to see neuro, did MRI.   Day nine, feeling even more a little bit better. Day ten, which is today, feeling even more a little bit better.  Saw neurologist for follow-up, he told me MRI turned out fine, everything looks good with brain.  Just stay very hydrated and relax, I should get better in a week.  I really went through hell, it was atrocious.  My doctors said could be vaccine-related, impossible to prove one way or the other.  I figured I?d report it, just in case there might be others in the country who went through the same thing.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I experienced stroke like symptoms on Saturday, April 10th, 15 days after receiving my first dose of the Pfizer vaccine. I experienced these symptoms starting around 1:30pm. First, my eyesight had been affected, I was seeing a black straight line aura in both of my eyes, I could not focus on any objects or people. I walked around my house and splashed some water on my face because I was feeling faint, I walked into the kitchen and said I?m going to pass out, I need to sit down, I sat on the floor... my partner was cooking me food and I asked him to get me water, but what came out was ?get me watermelon? from that point on, several of my sentences were not making sense and I was experiencing aphasia.  I was starting to freak out and my right thumb began to tingle and feel numb. My partner gave me .05 mg of Xanax because I was shaking uncontrollably. I became very cold. It took about 20-25 minutes to calm down. In that time, I tried to read words off of his phone and I could not verbalize out loud what specific words actually said, it made sense in my mind, but when I would try to read it out loud, it was wrong. My episode ended in about 25 minutes, while I was eating and then I went to the urgent care.
LAB_DATA: I went to the urgent care after my event and had an MRI, they suggest I do a follow up visit with various testing on Tuesday, April 13th. I had echo complete 2d bubble, MRI brain, CT head and neck. All lab results were cleared and no negative findings were found. I am currently being monitored with a heart monitor for the next 30 days.

37 yo obese dependent female with severe vasovagal reaction after a 30 minute wait time someone walking by noticed patient was not looking well and informed the observation staff. Nurse called for assistance and began talking with the patient.   Provider arrived and patient was pale, slumped in chair but conversive. Upon assisting patient to the floor she became unconscious and we laid her down. EMS was requested. Over the next few minutes had 3 episodes of LOC with brief ~5 seconds of breathing cessation and seizure like activity with significant head shaking sometimes involving upper torso followed by coughing and retching without actual vomiting. Due to this she was placed in left lateral recumbent position with the first episode. Each time she awoke she appeared confused but was able to answer questions. Oxygen was applied with pulse oximetry but unable to obtain BP during this time. After the third episode she suddenly asked what happened and mentation returned to normal.   Upon Fire/EMS arrival was conversing normally on the floor on her left side. Reported multiple food/environmental allergies and metformin allergy. History of suspected seizure but nothing proven.   Reported before her vaccine that last time she experienced a brief LOC hours ~12 hours after her first vaccine. She had arranged for someone to stay with her tonight in case she felt faint again.
PRIOR_VAX: Patient reported had syncope event after first dose of vaccine
ALLERGIES: Multiple Food Allergies/Environmental Allergies and allergy to metformin

This was Johnson & Johnson Vaccine.  I had the normal symptoms but it still felt very severe. I think there should be emphasis shared that symptoms might be severe. I believe the public should have a clear idea how severe. From 7pm to 12am I experienced extreme temperature changes, burning hot to very cold. I had the shakes. Headache. I took Advil which helped endure.  Buried myself in blankets with heater and heat on.  Drowsy. Experienced some dizziness. Now 3 days later I have some 'pings' here and there but uncertain if from vaccine. I feel these in my ovaries and my legs and my side. These are very subtle 'pings' (bit of pain but not much). Unsure if worth reporting but I think all this is important. Also, I have anxiety about the effect on this vaccine on the health of women and think it is very important that this is clear before pushing people -- more specifically young women, girls, babies -- to take this, and perhaps, any vaccine. I have been told from 5 friends they experienced heavy bleeding after taking the vaccine. They may have not all taken the J&J vaccine to be clear.  I do not feel great about having taken this vaccine.  I feel like i've put myself at risk of some other complications but of course, this is based on news and fear.  I just wanted to share this experience, and I hope that, if anything, the severity of symptoms might be more broadly shared.
LAB_DATA: NONE; i did not need to go to a doctor. My symptoms lasted within expected range of side effects for this vaccine

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On April 10th, 12 days after vaccination, at approximately 6pm, patient started having explosive diarrhea and uncontrollable gas. This subsided by the morning of the 11th. Monday the 12th, at 3am, patient was woken up to severe migraines (patient has no prior history of migraines or headaches). She described her pain as radiating-- like a bright, light house was being shined directly into her eyes in her sleep. This was combined with a pounding, pulsating feeling in the frontal lobe. Patient reported hypertension, nausea, and tingles in the tips of her fingers. These symptoms persisted throughout the day. On Tuesday the 13th, the same symptoms persisted. Patient heard the new CDC warnings about the Janssen vaccine, and concerned for her well-being, called her physician. Her physician directed her to go to the emergency room as soon as possible.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient woke up the morning of 04/13/21 and explained to his wife that he felt "foggy" mentally. He went about his morning chores on the farm. He came inside to sit in his recliner with his feet elevated for almost an hour.  At approximately 9:40 am, his wife observed that patient suddenly stiffened without warning and cried out. His arms stretched over his head in the chair and his legs stiffened like a board. His body was visibly contracted.  He continued to cry out. His eyes were closed, he was salivating, and his forehead was sweating.  His wife watched him move his arms suddenly to his lap, however, his fists were clenched tight.  She tried to get his attention by calling to him. She noticed his lips were turning blue. She continued shaking him, shouting and then slapped him. Patient did not respond.  She called 911. After 7 minutes, he finally relaxed some and started snoring loudly in the chair. He continued sleeping soundly for about 10 minutes while she waited for EMS to arrive.  The wife did elevate his head , as she was told by 911 to do so.  She was not able to wake him up during this time period. When the EMS arrived, he was just starting to move. They got him up to stand and he was able to verbalize his need to go to the restroom.  They arrived at the hospital at approximately 10:25 am and was released after testing at approximately 2:30 pm.
LAB_DATA: 04/13/21 lab work, EEG, EKG,  MRI scheduled for 04/19/21
CUR_ILL: March 12, 2021 had a pacemaker placed internally for AV Block
ALLERGIES: Ibuprofen causes Headache No known drug allergies

SYMPTOM_TEXT: * Arm was very sore for about the first 10 minutes.  Moving it reduced it pretty quickly and was no worse than a minor ache for most of the next day or so. * Had a mild headache before the shot (believe due to not having had caffeine that day yet) * At about 6 pm on 4/10, lost appetite due to mild nausea (just enough to not want to eat but not enough to vomit) * At about this time I noticed I also started to feel a little winded, akin to walking just briskly enough that you have to breath harder than if you're just sitting / resting.  It did not get any worse than this however, so I opted to keep a close eye and see if it eased (which it would by end of Sunday, 4/11) * At about 8:30 pm on 4/10, noticed I felt warm, had a fever between 100.4 to 100.8 * Also around 8:30 pm I noticed that pain I normally feel from my herniated discs and pinched nerves (L4/L5 L5/S1) just ACHED and was more painful than normal. * Started feeling tired (I'm usually up until around 1-2 am, and I was ready to go to bed by 9pm on 4/10)  Also felt a little forgetful / hard to concentrate on anything * When I went to bed, I noticed that my eyes were very sensitive to the white light from my monitor.  This is usually a sign of a painless migraine with auras that essentially blind me for about a half hour.  I did not have auras, though my headache was steadily getting worse to the point I suspect it might have actually been a migraine) * At about 12:30 am on 4/11, the headache got to the point where I could no longer ignore it (best I can describe is it felt like someone was trying to peel my skull of like you would an orange) so I took 200 mg of Ibuprofen.  I also by this point had a fever of 102, though it would drop to 100.5 or so within a few minutes of taking the Ibuprofen. * At about this point the arm starting aching a lot more, I assume because I wasn't using it while sleeping.  It felt like someone had punched me multiple times hard in the same spot. * I felt much better on the morning of 4/11.  However as the day continued I felt more and more tired.  My temperature was higher than normal but very mild; it stayed around 99.8 for most of the day that I took it.  By Monday, 4/12 I felt mostly fine aside from my arm aching worse than it did when I first got the shot.  Now on 4/14 its pretty much no longer achy.

The weakness disappeared within 48 hours of injection.  the pain in the arm lasted 14 days with less each day.

I went To my doctor and had all normal tests. They gave me Meclizine and Zofran. They also referred me to an ENT. Symptoms began to lessen a few days but still not enough to drive. After visiting the ENT, they diagnosed me with vestibular neuritis. They have me on steroids now and Valium if needed. I'm also getting an MRI and going to receive some balance therapy. I have No history of this and am typically a very healthy person who doesn't take  any medications. I believe That my body responded to the vaccine like a virus and caused this crazy reaction.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 30 minutes after receiving the J & J vaccine, my left arm, and then left leg began to feel heavy and intermittently tingly (that was not what I consider the adverse event, but I want to give you the full context). Then approximately 40-45 minutes after the vaccine was administered, I was sitting and typing on my computer when out of the blue I felt considerable  tightness in neck. The sensation began at the base of my neck and moved upwards across my neck and rose into my head. At that point, it felt like my neck and head were in a vise. That continued while at the same time it felt like there was a great deal of pressure directly on my sinuses.  This all continued for 1-2  minutes, at which point the tightness in the necks  diminishing until I  did not feel it any long. The tightness and pressure in my head lasted another 10 minutes or so. It gradually diminished, before fully dissipating after. The entire event lasted about 12-15 minutes and was very scary, as nothing like that has ever happened to me. Once it was over, I continued to feel heaviness and intermittent tingling in my left arm and left leg for another couple of hours. By the next day the heaviness was gone, but I was a bit congested and had a headache.  I didn't know who to report this to until the J & J vaccine administration was halted and it occurred to me that maybe my experience  should be documented and reported. A friend found this website for me.
ALLERGIES: Penicillin. I got hives all over my body at age 11 after taking Augmentin and was told to assume it was an allergy to penicillin. Haven't had any penicillin based antibiotics since.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 29 yo Female reported after last vaccine hives that resolved next day with Benadryl and single brief dizziness described as insignificant before vaccine.  Upon walking to the bathroom during the 30 minute wait time, escort noted patient appeared to be in need of assistance so he offered her a chair. Upon sitting, she slumped against him so he asked for medical assistance. EMS called. On the ground patient was unresponsive with shallow breathing; neck was hard to move but attributed to her large bun. Stethoscope used to hear breath sounds as nurse reported she was breathing but did not appear to be strong breaths. Pulse ox 96% or higher with BP appropriate, HR in 90s.  She awoke to sternal rub, nurse asked her if she had difficulty breathing after noting her jaw was rigid and unable to open. Patient indicated yes to difficult breathing so epinephrine was given.  ~ 30 seconds after epinephrine patient alert and breathing deeply, began to respond to questions.  After reporting breathing was still moderately difficulty (a few minutes later), epinephrine second dose given. Patient transport via EMS.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: March 9, 2021: 3:30am:  Woke up with chills and feeling very cold 7:00am:  Woke up with fever of up to 103F and extreme fatigue and headache which lasted during the day. Took Benadryl twice (6 hours apart) and the hives calmed down and eventually went away during the course of the day.  March 14, 2021 1.30am:  Woke up with itchy hives on my torso and back.  Took Benadryl once again.  I called my physician and was instructed to take Cetirizine for the next couple of days (10mg at 1x per day).  Symptoms subsided.  March 23, 2021 4:00am:  Woke up with itchy hives on the left side of my torso and across my back and my groin area and upper thighs.  Called my physician once again who instructed to take Cetirizine for a course of 2 weeks.  No symptoms while taking Cetirizine.  Stopped taking Cetirizine on April 2.  April 6, 2021 6:00am. Woke up with itchy red patches (with very small bumps) in localized areas of the body (ie on my hand, on my right leg, and areas near my armpits.  These lasted a little while with intense itchiness...would subside to just having red patches, and another area of the body would manifest red itchy patches.    The above lasted several days as I wanted to see if this would go away on its own.   On April 9th, called my physician to advise of the continued itchy patches which seem to come and go in different areas.  Advised to take Cetirizine once again for another 2 weeks once a day.

1 April, woke up at 0800 with slight headache and felt fatigued but most noticeably my voice sounded weird and my throat was extremely hoarse while talking in work meeting and I had to constantly cough to clear it. I was having a bit of trouble swallowing as well. In the afternoon, my headache got worse and I had diarrhea. Around 7:45pm I started feeling extreme itchiness and swelling in my tongue. This didn't improve, so I took 25mg Benedryl at 8:20pm, at which time my vitals were normal, but noticeably lower than usual with a HR of ~60, BP of 100/70, O2 sat 99% and normal temp. I also took another 1000mg Tylenol at 9:30pm and went to bed.  2 April, 0730 woke up and my throat and tongue started swelling again and were very itchy. I began have difficulty breathing and swallowing saliva. I also could not swallow a banana easily, so I stopped eating it. I also had some wheezing that would only go away with a cough. Took 25mg more of Benedryl and went to urgent care immediately because breathing was becoming increasingly difficult.   Treatment: At urgent car I was diagnosed with anaphylactic reaction due to vaccination and given another 25mg Benedryl injection and 10mg Prednisone. Vitals were BP:144/90, HR:83, TMP 98.5. Doctor considered epinephrine instead of Benedryl but "didn't want to have to send me to the ER". I was monitored for about 45 minutes and while my difficulty breathing did not improve much, it also did not worsen. I was sent home with Medrol steroid pack, Atarax and an EpiPen. My breathing ability did not return to normal until about ~3 days later.
LAB_DATA: None yet, upcoming allergist appointment to review further.
HISTORY: Unknown/diagnosed auto-immune issue: ongoing fatigue, muscle stiffness, headaches, joint pain, short term memory issues, spinal inflammation, nerve pain, numbness and tingling in arms and feet, electrical sensation down neck and across back periodically.
ALLERGIES: Coconut: anaphylaxis; latex: skin irritation, hives.

She had electrolyte derangements including hypokalemia and AKI and was admitted to hospitalist service with surgery consulting.  She improved with NG tube decompression, IV fluid resuscitation, and electrolyte repletion.  On 3/19 she underwent umbilical hernia repair and was found to have an incarcerated umbilical hernia. She does have chronic thrombocytopenia due to her cirrhosis, with last available baseline platelet count in the 50s.  She did not have any significant bleeding postoperatively.  She did not have any signs of decompensation of her cirrhosis.  MELD Na is 13, with less than 2% 90-day mortality. SYMPTOM_TEXT: On APRIL 1, 15 days after injection, I developed chest pressure and a burning sensation in the area of my sternum. The pressure worsened the next day to the point I asked to be taken to the ED at the hospital. My blood pressure was 187/92, I had some irregularities in my EKG. After lab tests for cardiac issues it was determined I was not having a heart attack. I then met with my PCP on April 7 to discuss this. We were wondering if it was anxiety. During this time from April 1 to present I have had marked soreness in both underarm lymph nodes and intermittent chest pressure. After another exchange with my PCP she confirmed that it could also be a possible response to the Moderna vaccine #1. Today, April 14, I had an echocardiogram stress test that was equivocal and it was determined to be safe, I should have a CT scan to make sure there is no issues in the arteries.  The cardiologist also agreed this could be an "inflammatory response" to the vaccine even though I was highly anxious during the test.  I say this to be fair and not wearing blinders. I would like to point out that the morning I awoke with chest pain, I was not experiencing anxiety. That came after my worry about what could be causing  it. I am only completing this form now because I feel it warrants the idea that there is vaccine involvement. By the age of 59 you tend to know your body. Thank you.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient came in for vaccine with his son. During the screening, the patient's son answered all of the questions regarding the patient. The patient's son denied any previous serious reactions to medications including the components to the vaccine. Only medical condition the patient's son mentioned was hypertension. The patient was vaccinated, and appeared fine. Once he got to the waiting area, he stated, "I feel hot." His coat was removed, the manager was notified,. We gave the patient something to drink, a snack, and a cold icepack. Once the patient's condition continued to decline, vital signs were assessed. Blood pressure was 140/110, pulse oximetry was 87% on room air, and patient was placed on oxygen. I notified the manager to go grab the doctor as I was helping the patient. The doctor brought a glucometer to make sure the patient was not hypoglycemic, and the result was 117 mg/dL. At this point the patient was diaphoretic, and complaining of pain in his abdomen. He also complained of nausea. The squad was alerted, and came to get the patient. At this point the patient's pulse ox was 53% on 6L of oxygen. Patient's family was present with the patient, and the patient was then transported to the hospital via EMS.
LAB_DATA: Vital signs were assessed and glucose to rule out hypoglycemia. The doctor ruled out anaphylaxis so therefore the patient did not receive any medication under our care.
HISTORY: Hypertension. Patient's son stated, "He is really healthy, I think he is healthier than me"

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I couldn't sleep the night of the day that I got the vaccine due to body aches and chills, and general feeling of discomfort. The next day I had a low fever that lasted the entire day, along with the body aches, chills, headache, nausea and soreness around the injection site -- basically, I felt flu-like. The fever didn't break until the following night around 1:30-2 a.m. -- so, 24 hours after symptoms started, and heading into the second day following my vaccination. I noticed the lymph nodes in both arm pits were painfully swollen, as well, which was not a side effect that I was warned about, so it freaked me out. The node in my left arm pit -- the arm where I got the vaccine -- was  more swollen and painful than the right arm. And that swelling did not leave until three days after my vaccine.   In short, I was feverish and ill the night I got the vaccine, and all of the following day after getting the vaccine. I still felt nauseated and had a headache two days after my vaccine -- which is when my lymph nodes in my under arms were also noticeably swollen and painful -- but the fever was gone. Three days out from the vaccine, the flu-like symptoms were gone, except for headache and fatigue. All told, I missed two days of work, and was "down for the count" feeling sick for three days.

Soon after stating this, patient stopped responding to questions, and her eyes were noted to be "blank," and were staring off to the ride side. No tonic/clonic activity noted. This seizure like activity was noted to last about 1 minute. Patient began answering questions again and was AOx4. Vital Signs remained stable during this seizure like activity. After a few minutes of talking with patient about her health history, writer noted patient having another "blank seizure," episode. Again, patient was not responding to questions and her eyes were noted to be "blank," and were staring off to the right side. No tonic/clonic like activity noted during this episode. Writer noted this episode to last about 2 minutes. Patient began answering questions again and was AOx4. Vital Signs remained stable during this seizure like activity. During this time, hives started to appear on patients left side of her face and front side of her chest and when patient began answering questions again after this seizure like activity, she started itching at the hives. 50mg Benadryl was given IM in her Right arm. EMS was called to site to assess patient and patient care was handed off to EMS staff.

Sunday afternoon, March 22, I started having severe stomach pain, but I thought it was gas. The pain progressively got worse (located in my upper right abdominal quadrant, under ribs, radiating to right side of back and under right arm). By Wednesday, March 24, I went to urgent care. They thought it was a gallbladder issue and sent me immediately to the emergency room. I went to the emergency room at the same location I received a vaccine, . After a full work up, they ruled out I didn't have gallstones, kidney stones, a PE, or anything of the sort. They sent me home. The pain continued to get worse, I was vomiting from the pain. I have had smoothies and saltine crackers, and some soup, for the last month at this point. I'm not able to eat regular food without severe stomach distress. My bowel movements a few days after March 24, were constipated then diarrhea. Then constipated again, and diarrhea. I've been very hydrated - now that my gastroenterologist RX'd Zofran. Before that, i couldn't drink water without feeling nauseous.   I woke up Sunday, March 28, to the pain in my side, which happens often, but this time when I woke up, my heart was pounding out of my chest. I grabbed my finger monitor nearby, and my heart rate was at 211pbm (o2 was 94-99), for several minutes. It eventually went down into the low 100s. once i was able - i immediately had my roommate help me into a car to go to the hospital again and get checked out. At the hospital, EKG showed sinus tachycardia, and they noted my abdominal pain had gotten worse, but at that point, nothing else could be done. I'm now seeing Gastrointestinal specialists, and a cardiologist, but testing has yet to be resulted. I still have abdominal pain. I have also had a severe headache, the entire near Month since the first shot. Hydration & Tylenol help 50% of the time, other times it just doesn't go away.  It should be noted, that I did get my second vaccine shot, even though my stomach still hurt. The pain in my stomach has gotten manageable over the last three weeks, but part of this is just me getting used to it. I have also been prescribed a medication to help with the nausea & another medication to help with stomach cramping/gallstones by my gastroenterologist. these do not change my pain level at all.  Within three hours of getting the second vaccine shot, the stabbing pain came back in my stomach again. It was not a thought in my head that it was vaccine related until this second shot - or if it is vaccine related- but the fact that it came back with such strength right after the second shot leads me to make this report. My pain is now, six days after the second shot, following the same trajectory as after the first shot. my BM are normal. I would have gone to the emergency room for this pain by now, but seeing that it's following the same symptoms & timeline as last time, I haven't.  I have let my primary doctor know, which is the doctor listed on this form. I have not seen him since getting the vaccine. But we have been in email communication. I've also let my gastroenterologist know this information. For now, I don't have any any course of action, except waiting for testing to be resulted from the gastroenterologist. I am also on an extended holter monitor. The intense stabbing feeling coming back almost immediately, the same afternoon that I got the second shot, is what leads me to make this report. It seems as though the second shot restarted my symptoms back to worse again, but, they have NOT fully gone away in the 3 weeks after the first shot.  I did have a fever and fatigue the first 48 hrs after 2nd shot; fatigue & no fever after 1st shot. I have tested negative to 4 PCR &2 rapid Covid tests given in this time period.

was observed post Covid-19 immunization for approximately 1 hr and 45min. Next BP was 184/91 HR 75. needed to go to the ladies room ambulated to rest room with nurse in attendance. No notable issue with gait.  The patient stated that she was feeling better but the blood pressures where elevated. Decided to ask EMT to do a manuel BP in the right  arm BP 160/82. Even though  was verbal, her responses where vague. One minute she felt fine then she was dizzy. was encouraged to call someone, but she felt she might be able to make it. There was a concern with her driving her self home.  EMT performed a cognitive test she stated the wrong year and did not know who the president was when asked in two separate assessments. They also performed a neuro assessment which was uneventful. EMT tried to contact sons but were unable too and patient could not find her phone where we could call a neighbor.  EMT suggested that she should go to the ED to be evaluated to be on the safe side and she agreed.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Immediately at 15 minutes: blurry vision; felt off and felt loopy (out of it);  I was dropping food on myself as I was eating. My pupils were really small. I felt out of it. Finally I got home (son drove me). I had mild chest pains and heart racing (had this initially, too). And the chest pains and heart racing kept happening off and on through the night. I had headaches that night and I felt nauseated. Next day, I had to wear sunglasses inside my  house as I was light sensitive and my pupils remained small. I still felt body aches and nausea but the eyes were the biggest concern...shining light by my eyes didn't make my pupils bigger. The light that came off my phone aggravated my eyes and my head. Thursday, I still had nausea but headache wasn't bad with Tylenol. Those full two days all I did was sleep. Friday, I felt like things were mild and Tylenol was helping. I called heathline for my eyes. As those still weren't improving. I got into my eye doctor for an exam (4/9). There was no inflammation and he decided to dilate my eyes. Of course, my eyes were blurry and my eyes responded to that dilation. I napped after returning home. My pupils after the nap were finally responding. I still had a little light sensitivity in my eyes but not as much as I had had and pupils were doing what they should with light. So this was 3 1/2 days later. I still do get mild headache and mild chest pain - it comes and it goes. I have a doctor appt - general check up  - that was already scheduled for tomorrow and he will examine for chest pain.
LAB_DATA: Eyes were dilated on by eye doctor - 4/9/2021 -  -   -
OTHER_MEDS: Synthroid - every day; Allertec - generic allergy med
CUR_ILL: I had a sinus infection and I was given antibiotics  - I was off of the medication about a week or so before the vaccine

Preliminary: I received the COVID Pfizer vaccine at Center on both Feb 17 and Mar 12. On April 6 I had leb tests performed by Quest Labs, and received the results on April 7.  My iron readings were quite low: Iron Total: 37 {normal range 50-180}, % Saturation: 13 {normal 20-48}; Ferritin 14 {normal 24- 380}. My last test prior was June 27, 2019 when the results were 76, 32 and 33 respectively.  Tomorrow I see my PCP physician and will discuss these results with him. My concern is that Ferritin, for example, is related to mRNA factors and the Pfizer CoViD vaccine is related to mRNA technology.  As I say, this is just preliminary prior to seeing my PCP, and he may wish to pursue this. I felt that I should let you know in case there are other vaccine / ferritin reports.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received shot and made her way from the clinical room to the observation area for the required observation period she walked back to the clinical room while another patient was being placed in the room and said she felt light headed, nauseated and dizzy . We had her sit back down and and elevate her feet in the waiting area while we moved the next patient out.  She was coherent and talking and said she felt nauseated and we moved her back to the clinic room and had her lie down on the carpet with her feet elevated. A few minutes went by and she reported that she felt her skin was hot and tingly.  We called for emergency services and began to attempt to take her bp. Pt appeared normal and reported no issues with her airway. She was speaking normally and answering question  appropriately.  The paramedics arrived and monitored her bp while lying down, sitting and standing. Her bp presented as elevated with tachycardia. Paramedics performed a blood glucose test which showed a low reading within normal limits. Patient reported not having eaten since breakfast. Pt's o2 saturation was "excellent" and she declined transport to hospital when offered by paramedics. No drugs were administered by pharmacy nor paramedics.
LAB_DATA: Blood pressure was monitored while laying down, sitting, and standing  all were slightly elevated with normal lowering  (still elevated) upon standing. O2 sats were normal. Blood glucose was low but within normal limits. 04/14/2021
CUR_ILL: HIGH CHOLESTEROL. HISTORY OF ANXIETY AROUND INJECTIONS.
HISTORY: HIGH CHOLESTEROL, IVF COMPLETED APPROX. 2 YEARS PRIOR

I also was experiencing allergy/asthma like symptoms that included difficulty breathing and shortness of breath that worsened over time I couldn't speak in full sentences or laugh I was unable to walk 10 steps without gasping for air, after a couple of days of trying to maintain and cope with my theses symptoms. I couldn?t take it anymore, as I was preparing myself to go to the emergency room. I got into the shower the steam from the shower felt like it was suffocating me and I passed out my children took me out of the bathtub and rushed me to the emergency room where I was given several tests that include x-ray, CAT scan, artery bloodwork and vein bloodwork. I was being treated for asthma and given several different breathing treatments and steroids, unable to keep my stats at a decent level and the hard rebound even after continuous treatments, I was admitted because the breathing treatments were not effective. I am still uncertain of the ?actual outcome? the Hospital doctors treated me for an asthmatic episode and gave me directions how to handle my asthma i was prescribed prednisone and referred  to my primary that would then refer me to a pulmonologist and cardiologist. At the hospital I was told that there was black spots on my lungs I was told that I was being treated for infection, but then also told it could be pneumonia no certain  answer was ever given and i was given and antibiotic and was also told that I needed to see my primary for a way to maintain my asthma. The antibiotics seem to work for a couple of days and again I'm back to having difficulty breathing, shortness of breath, muscle pain soreness and mild lingering headaches. Around 06:00 pm, which was about 9 hours after having received the J&J vaccine, I began having a slight fever and chills.  The most pain I had was in the back of my legs.  Both of my calves felt as if they had both been kicked and were badly bruised.  It was painful to walk for about 48 hours/2 days (Sunday - Monday).  That was the first time in my life that I had that kind of pain in my back calves.  Never had before from running or walking.  Then around 09:00 pm on Tuesday, a reddish dot appeared on the left side of my cheek.  I thought it was just a big zit.  But the following day, the dot got bigger, and looked like a scratch.  On Wednesday, it was definitely a scratch-like shape (2 lines, less than an inch long) and had begun to feel itchy.  That was when I had realized that it had the same pus-like dotted features of a cold sore.  But oddly, it's not right next to either side of my lips.  Instead, it is further down, towards the left side of my chin.  It is very rare for me to get cold sores.  I can't remember when my last one was, as it was years ago.  So I am wondering if this cold sore is due to having received the vaccine.  The fever, chills, and leg pain have not returned after those first 2 days.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received vaccine and was asked to move to observation area.  Shortly after sitting down the patient came back to pharmacy counter and stated he was feeling dizzy.  Just as the pharmacist was telling him to sit back down he fainted and fell on the floor.  He recovered rather quickly (matter of seconds?) and tried to sit up right away.  Pharmacist asked him to stay on the floor for a moment, the store's first responder (MIC) was called over to pharmacy.  After a minute of sitting on floor the patient got up on his own accord and transferred to a nearby chair.  His BP was taken twice per emergency protocol of pharmacy.  Patient initially appeared calmmy and BP  was 132/81, pulse 44, respirations 18 at 12:25p.   BP was 142/89, pulse 48, respirations 16 at 12:35.  Patient was given both a water and a Gatorade while he was seated.  Patient stated he had not eaten anything yet for the day.  Patient was repeatedly offered medical services (i.e. "Do you want a medic? Do we need to call an ambulance?") The patient repeatedly refused any further medical treatment.  After further observation patient was able to stand, check out at the pharmacy and left the store on his own accord.

stroke; cognitive difficulties; Information has been received from a lawyer regarding a case in litigation, concerning a patient of unknown age at the time of the events and unknown gender. The patient's past medical history, concurrent conditions and concomitant therapies were not reported. On or about 21-OCT-2012, the patient was inoculated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine (strength, lot #, expiration date, dosage, route of administration, and anatomical location were not reported), at a pharmacy, for routine health maintenance and for its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (herpes zoster). Shortly after receiving zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine, the patient suffered a stroke (cerebrovascular accident) and had continued to suffer from cognitive difficulties (cognitive disorder) as a result. As a result of those symptoms, the patient was seen and treated by medical providers in and at the time of the report was still under their care. As a direct and proximate result of defective zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine, the patient's symptoms had resulted in physical limitations not present prior to using vaccination. The patient also experienced mental and emotional distress due to resulting physical limitations and seriousness of the patient's condition. As a result, the patient sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence, the patient suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. As a direct and proximate result, the patient had suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations; and other economic and non-economic damages.  The lawyer reported the cerebrovascular accident and cognitive disorder as disabling events.  Upon internal review, the event cerebrovascular accident was considered to be medically significant.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 4/10/2021 experienced some right side facial paralysis upon waking.  Called urgent care who directed me to go to a hospital as soon as possible and asked about all events leading up to this, noting that the vaccine may potentially have this side effect, as written in the medical journal.  Went to the ER, they put me in stroke protocol, did CAT scan, negative results, blood tests (including for Lyme), MRI to look for tumors after the CAT scan was negative, and an echocardiogram as they detected a new heart murmur never present before. MRI showed Bell's palsey in one facial nerve, all other tests are negative, including for Lyme's disease, a common cause.  I am still experiencing it, and am on Valtrex (anti viral) and Prednisone, but the symptoms still exist. There is no other change in my life or health, the only thing I've done differently is have the vaccine (for which we are grateful).
LAB_DATA: CAT Scan, Blood work including a lyme panel, chest Xrays, MRI - all done on 4/10, Echocardiogram (4/11).

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The patient was reportedly in her USOH until she received the first dose of the Pfizer vaccine on 1/4. She woke up the following morning with a terrible headache and photophobia, later in the day developing myalgias and generalized weakness, followed by possible fever (did not take home temp). She describes the headache as a throbbing holocranial ache that is worse if she bends down She states the headache never really went away fully over the ensuing days, and she did begin to notice blurred vision in her right eye; she eventually presented to  Medical Center on 1/9, where she was tested for COVID-19 and found to be negative - her symptoms were attributed to a vaccine reaction and she was sent home. She continued to have a terrible headache and blurred vision, and so returned to Medical Center on 1/12. She then presented to another Hospital she was admitted for frequent falls in the context of elevated blood pressure. Workup there included a head CT, which was unremarkable. She was discharged with home PT.   On the day of presentation, she fell at physical therapy. Now with pain from R knee down. No numbness in the leg. States leg twisted when she fell. No head strike or LOC. States pain with attempted ambulation. This resulted in her presentation to the ED at a Medical Center on 1/27/21.   On evaluation, she endorsed a headache, holocranial, throbbing, 5-6/10 (has been 10/10). Denies frank positional component. Not worse at any certain time of day. +Blurred vision, worse on the R. +photophobia, not phonophobia. Also complains of pulsatile tinnitus happening almost daily, R-sided, worse when bending down. Denies nausea or vomiting. Denies neck pain or stiffness.   Exam was notable for significant peripheral vision loss in R>L eye and bilateral papilledema. She was seen by ophthalmology with documentation of formal visual field testing (reports included). MRV with filling defects in straight, sagittal, and R transverse sinuses; MRI without FLARE changes, reassuring for no obstruction and/or infarct.
LAB_DATA: MRI/V -- 1/27/21 -- Nonocclusive subacute clot in the right transverse sinus and smaller  linear areas of likely clot in the proximal straight sinus and distal  superior sagittal sinus. The sinuses however are patent.   No evidence of cranial hemorrhage.   No evidence of orbital mass with equivocal papilledema associated with the  left more than right optic nerve. With the empty sella, pseudotumor  cerebri should be considered.   Normal intracranial arterial vasculature.   Platelet count was 332,000 on 1/27/21.   Peripheral infectious workup was negative. ESR was highly elevated (119); TSH wnl. ANA+, anti-centromere+ (remainder of hypercoagulable workup summarized below).  Summary of workup sent: -> Protein C (activity 164 - mildly elevated) &S antigen total 122, free 144 -> factor II (prothrombin) mutation 20210 negative -> Factor V Leiden - 69 (normal) -> plasminogen activity - 124 (normal) -> antithrombin activity - 88 (normal) -> antiphospholipid Ab - pan-neg > B2 glycoprotein Ab - negative > Lupus anticoag panel - pan -neg except Pt mixing study, which expected given patient was on heparin at the time -> ANA - positive, centromere pattern, 1:640 -> ANCA - negative -> RF - <7 -> dsDNA - negative -> APL abs as above
HISTORY: obesity (BMI 62, s/p gastric bypass mid-2020), OSA on CPAP, HTN, T2DM (A1c 7.4%), anemia, depression, gallstones, irregular menses, and tobacco abuse

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On the fourth day after the injection, I experienced blurry vision that was relatively mild over the course of maybe an hour. The next day, the same thing. The following day, March 25 (vaccine was 3/19) I experienced transitory vision field impairment in the left eye which came in from the left periphery. This came and went over the course of about 1-1/2 hour, including throughout the visit to my doctor.  Prior to this, both my 21 year old daughter (who was vaccinated the same time as I was), experienced sudden migraines at the same time.   On Saturday 3/27 I began to experience a twitch/pulse which is still happening intermittently in my left cheek.   I received the second dose of the vaccine April 9th. The twitching continues. Additionally, I had sharp pain across the length of the sole of my foot that was brief. It recurred three times.   I've had a thorough workout which does not indicate the source of the problem.   I've begun taking baby aspirin, but experience minor bleeding if I take it more than once weekly.

HISTORY: Migraines, which occur very rarely. Started at age 45 or so.  18 months ago,  I experienced a series of severe nose bleeds over the course of several months During that time frame, I experienced a similar visual impairment. Complete medical exams never turned up a definite explanation.

After the 1st dose, about a week or so afterwards I developed an awful painful red rash around my mouth. It burned and was very uncomfortable. My lips started to peel off severely. I went to the dermatologist who tested samples for fungal, viral, and bacterial infections and they all came back negative. While we waited for the tests to come back she gave me an anti-fungal nystatin cream to treat the lips which within days cleared up the red/peeling. Then I got my 2nd dose on 04/05/21 and within a few days after that I started to develop pain and soreness inside of my mouth and white patches around my tongue, cheeks, etc. which made eating very uncomfortable. I went back to my dermatologist and she said it looked like oral thrush and has given me a nystatin mouth wash to use for the next 7-14 days.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Got the vaccine, shortly after that had a feeling of having a novocaine shot numbing feeling from her right side of her arm, her shoulders, head/neck, and then to the left arm.  This then passed.  That evening she was tired, sleepy and then the next day she had a bad headache. (possibly related to menstrual cycle beginning).  She took Excedrin for that and when she woke up the 2nd day she was fine.    Then on 4/12/21 she had her hair pulled up and reached the back of her neck and felt a pimple like feeling on the back of her neck.  She then had her daughter look at her neck who informed her that she had a red rash, squeezed it and it popped and then noticed she had several on her neck.  She then had the numbness return that she had on the right hand side of her face, her arm and a little down her leg.  She went and got some Vitamin E ointment and rubbed it on the back of her neck, which seemed to resolve the rash eventually.  Then that numbness feeling went away within an hour or two.   The following night she also had recurrence of the same events from the previous day.  Last night 4/14/21, she had the rash again on the back of her neck, and had actually  moved down into her back area, down to her shoulder blade the same pimply type rash, and numbness down her side.  She now has the same feeling around her ear area.  She tried again the vitamin E ointment which did not help anything.  She then took a Vitamin D pill which did not seem to do anything either.  She woke up multiple times during the night as she still had the feeling and did not go away.  When she woke up she felt sort of okay, has the rash, had the feeling of having had a headache/achy feeling, and can feel the rash on the back of her neck again.    She has a call into her doctor to see if she can be seen.    She has also noticed that her right arm had some swelling around the elbow area, but last night's episode she could definitely tell that it was swollen and the skin tight in the upper inside of the elbow and up to about the armpit.
HISTORY: Asthma, hypothyroidism, Sjogren's syndrome, spinal stenosis.
ALLERGIES: Codeine (rash).  Breads, gluten stuff, tomatoes, pastas, (water retention).

When patient arrived in nurse's office, she stated she had experienced tingling in face, lips, and hands with the first dose.  Patient chose to continue with vaccination series and receive second dose.   She brought a personal Epi-pen and oral Bendadryl as contingencies.  Vaccination was given.  Patient remained in nurse's office and 6 minutes post vaccine administration she began to state that she was experiencing tingling in her face, hands, arms.  Within minutes, patient also stated that her throat was beginning to feel tight.  When asked if she wanted to administer her Epi-pen, she refused.  She then self-administered a single dose of oral, OTC Benadryl 25 mg.  Nurse asked if she wanted paramedics to be called and patient refused.  Within a few minutes of self administration of the Benadryl, she stated she felt her throat was constricting further.   Nursed then called 911 and continued to monitor patient until paramedics arrived.  Patient was again asked if she would take her Epi-pen and she refused again.  Patient stated that Benadryl had always been sufficient to control allergic reactions in the past.   Vitals:  BP 139/90 Pulse 98 Temp 98.0 Respiration rate was impossible to ascertain because patient was breathing irregularly.  Paramedics arrived and assessed the patient.  Patient stated that she was feeling better and refused to be transported to the hospital.    Patient remained in clinic until her spouse arrived and transported her home at approximately 10:45am.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received first dose of Pfizer vaccine and waited her required 15 min observation time. About 5 min after her injection she felt dizzy and lightheaded. RN assessed pt and gave her water, had her put her head back and legs up. After a few minutes she was feeling better until she started complaining of nausea and abdominal cramps. Her pulse was thready but pt was awake and alert, responding to questions. Patient elected to go to the ER via ambulance.
LAB_DATA: Differential diagnosis: Medication reaction, allergic reaction, less likely pancreatitis, less likely dehydration, General review: Laboratory data were reviewed and interpreted and the information was used to make clinical decisions. ED course details: Will order routine labs including a lipase to rule out pancreatitis we will also administer Pepcid for the patient's GI upset.  She demonstrates no sign of airway occlusion or compromise at this time.  Her uvula is midline and she has no stridor on exam.  She also has mild diffuse erythema or hives.  7:24 PM patient was re assessed she does not have any or throat swelling or any sensation that her throat is closing.  She has no hives.  Her lungs are clear to auscultation bilaterally.  Time she has been around approximately 2-1/2 hours post vaccine administration.  She has required no further intervention at this time.  Have recommended that she continue with some over-the-counter antacid medicine as needed.  And that she should follow-up with her PCP.  Have also advised her that if she has any symptoms of an allergic reaction which include generalized hives itching or sensation that her throat is closing or lip or tongue swelling she should return to the emergency department.  Patient is stable for discharge at this time with follow-up by her PCP. Discharge: The patient is ambulatory, alert, and understands directions. I had a detailed discussion with the patient and/or guardian regarding the historical points, exam findings, and any diagnostic results supporting the discharge diagnosis. Based on the patient's history, exam, and diagnositic evaluation, there is no indication for further emergent intervention or inpatient treatment.

Then by 4/12/21 he was not able to breath well at all and his wife took him to the ER.  In the hospital they did x-rays and found out that his lungs are full of blood clots and both legs have blood clots in them.  He was admitted and gave him Heparin drip for the 2 days to get the blood clots dissolved and was also on oxygen for 2 days.  He was discharged home yesterday with Xarelto, and was told that he would be on that for the rest of his life, and is on oxygen for sleep and when he's up and around, but if he's resting and feels he's breathing okay he can remove it.   They informed him that it would take approximately 2 months for all the blood clots to dissipate, and that he was full of blood clots, and had both legs and both lungs which are quite full.

I immediately felt dizzy, like I was drunk. At around 4pm, I started feeling wheezy. It felt like there was a mastiff sitting on my chest. I took some benadryl, which helped. The next day, the feeling persisted and I had a mild cough, especially while lying down. More benadryl. Same on the third day. I did not seek medical attention because I didn't think it was an extraordinary reaction and I have had much worse reactions to other things in the past that have been managed with benadryl. I thought what I was experiencing was an expected side effect based on the information I had been given. The feeling started to ease by the 4th day, but then the insomnia, mood swings, exhaustion and body aches set in. The cough was sporadic, but still present. Today, I still get the heavy chest feeling intermittently, activity doesn't seem to have any effect or cause. My arm still itches at the injection site and hurts when touched.  I went back to get my second dose on 4/9. When the nurse asked me if I had had any adverse reactions to the first one, I told her about the chest heaviness and coughing and the other symptoms. She stopped what she was doing and called her medical director. They both decided that the first response was enough of an anaphylactic reaction to be a caution for the second. They refused to give me the second dose because they thought the second would elicit a much worse reaction - possibly to the point of intubation. They told me that I would have to be evaluated by a physician and that I would need a "doctor's note" in order to get the second vaccine.
HISTORY: PCOS, Vertical Sleeve Gastrectomy in 2015, allergies
PRIOR_VAX: Flu vaccine - dizziness and disorientation, fever, trouble breathing
ALLERGIES: Ceclor, Tetracycline, Seafood (fish and shellfish), evergreens and their oils

As the day progressed The frequency increased and I began having a fever in the afternoon around 4:00 p.m.   The fever continue to increase into the night and reached a point around 102?F and was paired with loss of energy/lethargy. Temperature reach just above 103?F over the night but bounced to a low as 98?but stayed around a 101-102.  The night was filled with chills and it was highly challenging to sleep.   That Monday 4/11 brought serious headache to the frontal lobe and behind my eyes in a way of not felt before along with severe stomach cramps and frequent needs to go to the restroom due to diarrhea. There was also total loss of appetite. I was bed ridden and slept all day. The combined pain brought me to tears regularly.  I went to urgent care that afternoon and also took a covid test. That night the fever broke.  Tuesday 4/12  The fever dropped to roughly 99?F In the headache mostly went away But the stomach cramps became more severe . The stomach cramps may have been equally as bad the previous day but I don't recall due to the fever and lethargy. I began tracking the times of each stomach pain and restroom visit and my results show a frequency of stomach pain/craming every 10-15 min.  These  Pains also brought me to tears and i had no appetite.   On Wednesday there were also stomach cramps in the morning through the evening but they were much less frequent going from roughly once an hour to once every few hours

SYMPTOM_TEXT: No initial symptoms. Arm did not hurt. Felt fine initially. A week later, my left eye started to water profusely and itch as if I'd gotten something in it. Within the hour, lymph nod in front of left ear swelled up to the size of a bean. The next morning, additional nods swelled up under the ear by the jawline. The eye was no longer watering, but was and continues to experience sharp pain like pins stuck in it, very painful. Some blurring of vision.  It is only in one eye still. Eye is not red. Eye is not watering. It shows no signs of visible conjunctivitis, but  very irritated. The following day the left side of my face is swollen along with swollen glands.  Additionally, a rash ahs developed along my hairline, on the upper bridge of my nose, and on forehead. The rash on my nose presents like blisters, almost like poison ivy rash. I was not exposed to poison ivy. I do not have acne, so the outbreak on my forehead is unusual.  The rash has gotten progressively worse and spread every day since the onset of these symptoms four days ago. I still have no fever. No armpit swelling. Never experienced this before. There was no clear cause of this nor any known infection. Suspect it could be immune response to 1st covid-19 shot. I was very healthy when I took the first shot.  Was advised to take a Covid-19 test as the eye hurting is apparently a rare symptom of the virus. Took test yesterday. Awaiting results. But I have no respiratory symptoms. No fever. Do have some mild diarreah since receiving the vax. Feel fine physically other than these very painful facial symptoms.

Client was set up for 30 min monitoring after receiving vaccine. At the end of the monitoring period, she reported that she was feeling some tightness in the jaw, but no other symptoms.  Her monitoring period was continued. Initial vital signs taken, BP 160/90, P-59, SaO2-98%. After monitoring for 10 more minutes, she reported that her jaw did not feel tight any longer, but she had a slight feeling of numbness/tingling in the cheeks and tongue.  She did not report any other symptoms and was able to talk and swallow normally.  She did not develop any obvious facial swelling or rash/itching. She was administered Benadryl 25mg.  Vital signs were repeated BP 150/80, P-60, SaO2 98%.  She stated that she was feeling a bit better after the Benadryl was administered.  Her husband had accompanied her to the clinic and would drive her home, and she had family available at home.  She and her husband were instructed to call 911 if  she worsens, but she and husband were comfortable with how she was feeling and she then left the clinic in improved condition.  A follow-up call was placed on 4/15/21 and her symptoms had totally cleared up shortly after leaving the health department and she felt fine once she returned home. She was instructed to follow up with her physician regarding what happened and next steps.

This was my second dosage of the Pfizer vaccine. Upon the first vaccine, I did feel symptoms of throat swelling and difficulty swallowing that subsided without intervention and quickly. For the second vaccine that I received today, I experienced dizziness in the store and began to sweat. I left because the pharmacy staff did not seem to want to be bothered. Upon driving home, within about 15 minutes of getting the vaccine, I began to have nausea to the point that I had to stop and pull over. I vomited a small amount of my breakfast. Continued to feel shaky, dizzy, faint, excessive saliva and tearing of eyes. Upon arriving in my driveway, it was hard to walk up stairs. The nausea continued for about 1.5 hours but the weakness and feelings of faintness continue still after 2 hours after the vaccine. I had some tachycardia. It's hard for my eyes to look up and my eyes hurt when I move them. I had moments of feeling like I had a parietal vice on my head. I called the pharmacy to report all of this and only spoke with a pharmacy assistant. No pharmacist called to check on me. I am an RN so I have the knowledge needed to care for myself and seek medical attention if needed, but I have sympathy for those that are not and have their report of symptoms dismissed just as I did from the vaccine provider.

On Monday, 3/1/21, I did notice a slight difference and felt they were beginning to heal. During this time, I kept the lips moisturized nearly 24 hours a day, frequently waking at night due to pain. I moisturized with various topical ointments and petroleum jelly. I also, at times, took OTC Benadryl (3 doses total). As of today, 4/15/21, I feel 95% recovered, as there is still some dryness.  Throughout March, the healing continued and I reached about 90% healed by the beginning of April.

This wakes me up 3-4 times a night and continues to this day >3 weeks later.  I started Zeposia medication a few days before this shot. I didn't have this effect with my 2nd shot in my other arm.  I did use an ax to chop wood for 4 hours 2 days before the shot, and my arm was sore from that before the injection. It's possible this is unrelated to the shot altogether, and I did something to trigger some sort of carpal tunnel with the ax. I plan on discussing with my Dr at some point.
